18/03/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- A Serbian police officer was sentenced to 20 years in prison on Wednesday (17 March) for taking part in the 1999 execution of 14 ethnic Albanian civilians in Podujevo.
Sasa Cvjetan, a member of the Scorpions special operations unit, is only the fifth Serbian national to be convicted in connection with the Kosovo conflict.
In other news, the UN war crimes tribunal is due to sentence a former Yugoslav Navy admiral on Thursday.
Miodrag Jokic pleaded guilty in August to several counts of crimes against humanity in connection with the shelling of Croatia's Dubrovnik in 1991.
Prosecutors have recommended a sentence of up to ten years.
(AP, AFP - 17/03/04)
